is attachment "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
=============================================================

NAME
----

is attachment - This [Conditional Tag](/Conditional_Tags "Conditional Tags") checks if

SYNOPSIS
--------

This [Conditional Tag](/Conditional_Tags "Conditional Tags") checks if
an attachment is being displayed. An attachment is an image or other
file uploaded through the post editor's upload utility. Attachments can
be displayed on their own 'page' or template. For more information, see
[Using Image and File
Attachments](/Using_Image_and_File_Attachments "Using Image and File Attachments").

This is a boolean function, meaning it returns either TRUE or FALSE.

USAGE
-----

` <?php is_attachment(); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `(boolean)` 
:   True on success, false on failure.

EXAMPLES
--------

    <?php
    if ( is_attachment() ) {
        // show adv. #1
    } else {
        // show adv. #2
    }
    ?>

NOTES
-----

-   See Also:
    [is\_singular()](/Function_Reference/is_singular "Function Reference/is singular")
-   For more specific checking of the attachment see: [Function
    Reference/wp attachment is
    image](/Function_Reference/wp_attachment_is_image "Function Reference/wp attachment is image")

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: 2.0.0

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`is_attachment()` is located in `wp-includes/query.php`.

